00:32:12,840 --> 00:32:14,760
Oh, I'm looking in the wrong place.

335
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:18,761
Yeah, he says, this should sound familiar, top of 342.

336
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:25,960
Gentlemen, I cried, suddenly, speaking straight from my heart, look around you with the gifts of God, the clear air, the pure air, the tendergrass, the birds.

337
00:32:25,961 --> 00:32:27,561
Nature is beautiful and sinless.

338
00:32:27,561 --> 00:32:34,361
Only we have sinned, and we don't understand that life is heaven, that's here and now in the world, this paradise.

339
00:32:34,360 --> 00:32:41,160
We have only to understand that, and it will at once be fulfilled in all its beauty, and we shall embrace each other and weep.

340
00:32:41,160 --> 00:32:46,921
So that's Osima getting the stage one primitive Christian experience.

341
00:32:46,921 --> 00:32:56,521
But instead of going crazy from getting the stage one experience, which sounds pretty crazy there, he goes in the monastery where it's not crazy.

342
00:32:56,521 --> 00:32:57,320
And that's that.

343
00:32:57,401 --> 00:32:59,641
So now we get to stage two.

344
00:33:00,921 --> 00:33:04,521
And now we get something on 367.

345
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:08,520
Oh, he's telling them more about how everything is connected and so forth.

346
00:33:09,081 --> 00:33:10,841
He still holds that.

347
00:33:10,840 --> 00:33:22,761
But he holds it now in its Christianized language and in the institution of elders where people understand each other and don't have to go crazy.

348
00:33:25,001 --> 00:33:29,241
Now, I'm just summing up what I wrote here.

349
00:33:29,240 --> 00:33:38,521
Those who receive this ecstatic Christian experience, not yet Christian experience, have to institutionalize it and make it livable.

350
00:33:38,521 --> 00:33:43,160
And that's what the elders and the people in the monastery do.

351
00:33:43,360 --> 00:33:47,601
They start, it starts already when the New Testament tries to make sense of it.

352
00:33:47,840 --> 00:33:53,601
And in the monastery, they've got a whole ritual for doing with it, dealing with it.

353
00:33:53,601 --> 00:34:00,561
But it's in the second stage, and this is the next important point, they are corrupted by philosophy.

354
00:34:01,200 --> 00:34:03,521
This is not an important thing to Dostoevsky.

355
00:34:03,521 --> 00:34:05,281
I don't even know if he thinks about it.

356
00:34:05,280 --> 00:34:18,481
But Zosima not only talks in Christian terms about the afterlife and how God is watching you and how you should pray to Him, he says this to the old woman whose son has died, for instance, does it several times.

357
00:34:18,481 --> 00:34:24,641
But the worst thing he says is on 368, two-thirds down.

358
00:34:24,641 --> 00:34:36,401
It's interesting, just because if you aren't tuned into the stuff I'm telling you, you think, well, Zosima knows the truth, and Zosima says this, this must be what Dostoevsky believes.

359
00:34:36,401 --> 00:34:40,561
Well, this is what Dostoevsky believes, stage two Christianity is about.

